5|$|After Reagan's {{military}} buildup, the Soviet Union did {{not respond}} by further building its military because the enormous military expenses, along with inefficient planned manufacturing and collectivized agriculture, were already a heavy burden for <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy.</b> At the same time, Saudi Arabia increased oil production, even as other non-OPEC nations were increasing production. These developments contributed to the 1980s oil glut, which affected the Soviet Union, as oil was {{the main source of}} Soviet export revenues. Issues with command economics, oil price decreases and large military expenditures gradually brought <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy</b> to stagnation.|$|E
5|$|During the Khrushchev era, {{especially}} from 1956 through 1962, the Soviet Union attempted to implement major wage reforms intended to move Soviet industrial workers {{away from the}} mindset of overfulfilling quotas that had characterised <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy</b> during the preceding Stalinist period and toward a more efficient financial incentive.|$|E
5|$|By {{the time}} the {{comparatively}} youthful Mikhail Gorbachev became General Secretary in 1985, <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy</b> was stagnant and faced a sharp fall in foreign currency earnings {{as a result of}} the downward slide in oil prices in the 1980s. These issues prompted Gorbachev to investigate measures to revive the ailing state.|$|E
25|$|The ambitious {{objectives}} of the Third Five Year Plan hinged upon <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy's</b> importing large amounts of technology from the United States, which then supplied over 60% of Soviet machine and equipment.|$|R
40|$|The {{comprehensive}} {{improvement of}} the mechanism of economic management is an objective necessity in the present stage of <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy's</b> development. As K. U. Chernenko emphasized {{in a speech to}} voters on March 2, 1984, the party is most keenly interested in bringing about improvements in the management of the economy and in restructuring the mechanism of economic management in numerous areas. ...|$|R
