50|$|In 1985, {{following}} the Era of Stagnation, reform-minded Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev signaled {{the trend toward}} greater liberalization. Emigration increased following liberalizations passed in 1986. For example, the flow of ethnic Germans from the Eastern Bloc dramatically increased from 42,786 per year in 1986 to 202,673 in 1988. <b>The</b> <b>Soviet</b> Union was facing a period of severe economic decline and needed Western technology. Subsidies to foreign client states further strained <b>the</b> moribund <b>Soviet</b> <b>economy.</b>|$|R
