50|$|He {{graduated}} from Petrograd Polytechnical Institute in 1914. Until 1917 {{he worked as}} a socialist activist. After the October Revolution he worked on setting up <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> planned <b>economy</b> while he was appointed to a professorship in economics at the Moscow State University. In 1931 he became a member of <b>the</b> <b>Soviet</b> Academy of Sciences. Strumilin's educational background was in statistics.|$|R
